# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Workspace-root .env.local (gitignored — do NOT commit).
#
# Copy to `<workspace_root>/.env.local` and fill in per-developer values.
# Each lesson's Vite dev server reads this workspace-root file because every
# lesson's `vite.config.js` sets `envDir` to the workspace root. (Vite does
# NOT walk upward on its own — without that envDir setting this file would
# be silently ignored.)
# Same variable names work in production — set them as Netlify environment
# variables (or equivalent) for the deployed site.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Desmos API key (REQUIRED whenever a lesson embeds <DesmosGraph/> or the
# chatbot emits <<DESMOS>>). Obtain a free educational key at
# https://www.desmos.com/api and allow-list `http://localhost:*` (dev) plus
# your production origin in the Desmos dashboard.
#
# Without this key, `useDesmos` logs an error and every DesmosGraph renders a
# red "Desmos graph unavailable: VITE_DESMOS_KEY not configured" fallback.
VITE_DESMOS_KEY=

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Notes
# - The embedded tutor chatbot authenticates via the locally-installed
#   `claude` CLI (spawned by `_lesson-core/server/proxy.js`). No API key is
#   read from this file for chat.
# - Vite exposes any `VITE_*` variable to the browser bundle at build time.
#   Only put values here that are safe to ship to the client (Desmos key is
#   fine; origin restrictions live in the Desmos dashboard).
# - Non-`VITE_*` variables in this file are ignored by the browser; the
#   Express proxy does not read this file at all. (The proxy honors a
#   PROXY_PORT variable from its own process environment, not from here.)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
